<P><H1 align=center>APPLICATION VERIFICATION – DC012</H1>
<P></P>
<P><FONT color=red><B>NOTE: </B>fields 
shown in red are mandatory and must be completed to proceed</FONT>           </P>
<P>This screen asks a series of questions which are related to the <A href="HELP_MC010.asp#LendingCriteria">Lending criteria</A>, to help establish whether the applicant can proceed further. All 
questions have Yes / No radio buttons.</P>
<P><H3>Are all applicants resident in the UK?: </H3>application may not be able to proceed if the applicants are not UK 
resident. This will depend on the <A href="HELP_MC010.asp#LendingCriteria">Lending criteria</A>.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Are all applicants aged 18 or over?: </H3>applicants 
must be aged 18 or over to be able to take out a mortgage.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Is the mortgage amount for £30,000 or above?: </H3>This 
question relates to the minimum loan amount offered by the lender. An amount 
below this will not be sufficient borrowing for the lender.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Is the mortgage term 5 years or more?: </H3>many 
lenders have a minimum term of 5 years. Whether the application can proceed 
depends on the <A href="HELP_MC010.asp#LendingCriteria">Lending criteria</A>.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Is the property the primary residence?: </H3>application may not be able to proceed, or may be subject to different 
criteria, if it is not for a residential loan.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Have you found a property?: </H3>if the applicant has 
not yet found a property, different details will need to be taken (ie. property 
details cannot be taken)
<P></P>
<P><H3>OK: </H3>click ‘OK’ to lead to the next screen.

